TY  - JOUR
T1  - Edgeworth Expansions for Semiparametric Averaged Derivatives
AU  - Nishiyama, Y.
AU  - Robinson, P. M.
Y1  - 2000/07/01
PY  - 2000
DA  - 2000/07/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1468-0262.00142
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 931
EP  - 979
VL  - 68
IS  - 4
KW  - Edgeworth expansion
KW  - semiparametric estimates
KW  - averaged derivatives.
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1468-0262.00142
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - A valid Edgeworth expansion is established for the limit distribution of density-weighted semiparametric averaged derivative estimates of single index models. The leading term that corrects the normal limit varies in magnitude, depending on the choice of bandwidth and kernel order. In general this term has order larger than the n?1/2 that prevails in standard parametric problems, but we find circumstances in which it is O(n?1/2), thereby extending the achievement of an n?1/2 Berry-Esseen bound in Robinson (1995a). A valid empirical Edgeworth expansion is also established. We also provide theoretical and empirical Edgeworth expansions for a studentized statistic, where some correction terms are different from those for the unstudentized case. We report a Monte Carlo study of finite sample performance.
ER  - 

